text: rhino beetles looks good in xenagos

>>>
This card is horrendously awful and I'll tell you why.
Let's look at his abilities. He's kinda like Prossh, where he get's value by casting him from the command zone over and over. Except, unlike Prossh, you are forced to dump excess mana into him to get anything. Even then, he's just a vanilla beater for a turn without haste.
Let's assume you cast him and he's large. You move to attacks. You can graveyard hate yourself, bringing a creature back after attacks are declared, hitting, and then losing the token you created.
This means 3 things: 1) this is unplayable in a renanimation deck. Graveyard hating yourself to get a single thing back only once is horrendously bad. You can also only target yourself, so not only do you GY hate yourself, you have to have already casted something worth bringing back and big enough to even attack with and have it matter. You can bring back small things for their EtB effects, but why would you do that? They'd just swing for 1 or 2 and then be blocked, then you lose them forever and lose their potential value forever.
2) You bring the creature back post-attack. This means you can't get any value from anything like Etali who get's value 'on attack.' Even the dinosaur and other things that copy creatures on attack don't work.
3) The tokens aren't cards, so you can't bounce them to your hand or anything. They are guaranteed to exit the game forever through an absurd amount of ways. Additionally, they exit at end of combat, meaning you can't sacrifice them for value using sorcery speed things, nor can you copy them using things that clone creatures.
Let's pretend you use this in an aggro deck. That means you are playing this ASAP (so it's like a 3/3 if not barely better) and you're getting back 1/1s from things that maybe have EtB values? Also aggro decks want quick games, this card is aggro, but has an X cost.
This card is unplayble in every archetype that could want it. This is one of the worst commanders printed in the last several years.
Edit: oh my god its worse than I initially thought. Not only the above, but you can only 'reanimate' creatures with less power than this. So you can't even drop this early and get a cheap primordial etb. You have to dump shitloads of mana into this, wait a turn, and THEN you get to reanimate something that's weaker than it. If you have all that mana anyway, why not just cast what you need to?? This was such a design fail, christ.
